Summary: This section explains how to set up a VideoStreamPlayer node to play video files in Godot.
1. Create a VideoStreamPlayer node.
2. In the Inspector, load a .ogv file into the Stream property.
   Note: If your video is not in Ogg Theora format, refer to the recommended Theora encoding settings.
3. To play the video automatically when the scene loads, enable the Autoplay property. Otherwise, disable Autoplay and call the play() method from a script to control playback manually.
---CHUNK---
